        <item>
            <title><![CDATA[The 10 Best Things We Bought in the First Half of 2026 | Furniture & Appliances for a Newlywed Home]]></title>
            <link>https://ryotablog.jp/en/blogs/zakki/best-buy-2026-first-half</link>
            <guid>best-buy-2026-first-half</guid>
            <pubDate>Sun, 05 Jul 2026 21:55:26 GMT</pubDate>
            <description><![CDATA[A ranked countdown of our best buys from the first half of 2026! After getting married, we furnished our new home from scratch — furniture, appliances, and storage. Here are the top 10 purchases that genuinely raised our quality of life.]]></description>
        </item>
        <item>
            <title><![CDATA[How I Passed the JSTQB Foundation Level in 1.5 Months by Generating 535 Mock Exam Questions with AI]]></title>
            <link>https://ryotablog.jp/en/blogs/test/jstqb-foundation-study-method</link>
            <guid>jstqb-foundation-study-method</guid>
            <pubDate>Sat, 04 Jul 2026 05:06:27 GMT</pubDate>
            <description><![CDATA[A pass report for the JSTQB Foundation Level (CTFL) after 1.5 months of studying. Covers the textbook and free app I used, my generative-AI study method — building a question-authoring engine with Claude Code and drilling 535 questions — and how to check your pass/fail result online.]]></description>
        </item>
        <item>
            <title><![CDATA[Who Are Hitooshi's Members? Age, Income, Education, and Looks Based on a User's Real Experience]]></title>
            <link>https://ryotablog.jp/en/blogs/zakki/hitooshi-members</link>
            <guid>hitooshi-members</guid>
            <pubDate>Tue, 30 Jun 2026 09:34:18 GMT</pubDate>
            <description><![CDATA[What are Hitooshi's members really like? A user who actually got introduced to people lays out the age range, income, education ratio, and looks ("are there beauties / handsome men?") backed by official data and first-hand impressions. Material to judge in about 5 minutes whether someone who fits you is on the service.]]></description>
        </item>
        <item>
            <title><![CDATA[My Ultimate Household Finance System, Fully Explained (Married Couple, No Kids)]]></title>
            <link>https://ryotablog.jp/en/blogs/zakki/saikyo-kakei-system</link>
            <guid>saikyo-kakei-system</guid>
            <pubDate>Mon, 22 Jun 2026 00:10:00 GMT</pubDate>
            <description><![CDATA[A dual-income married couple (no kids) shares the household money system they built over three months, in interview format. SBI Sumishin Net Bank's purpose-specific accounts and auto-transfers, automatic Rakuten Card statement collection, and logging cash with a single LINE message. An engineer's 'minimum running cost' approach to household finances.]]></description>
        </item>
        <item>
            <title><![CDATA[[Curious About Reviews?] My Experience with Hitooshi Matchmaking Service (Referral Code Included)]]></title>
            <link>https://ryotablog.jp/en/blogs/zakki/hitooshi-review</link>
            <guid>hitooshi-review</guid>
            <pubDate>Tue, 11 Feb 2025 11:38:50 GMT</pubDate>
            <description><![CDATA[A review of the matchmaking service "Hitooshi". A Tokyo engineer shares his real matchmaking experience! Detailed explanation of the flow from 2-hour counseling to online meetings, reviews, reputation, advantages and disadvantages. Includes a referral code at the end.]]></description>
        </item>
        <item>
            <title><![CDATA[What Does Hitooshi's First Interview Ask? A User Explains the Questions, Flow, and Preparation]]></title>
            <link>https://ryotablog.jp/en/blogs/zakki/hitooshi-interview</link>
            <guid>hitooshi-interview</guid>
            <pubDate>Wed, 23 Apr 2025 05:03:00 GMT</pubDate>
            <description><![CDATA[A real user explains Hitooshi's first interview: the roughly 45-minute Zoom session, what you are asked (the questions), the flow up to the day, how to prepare, and dress-code tips. Includes a referral code for 5,000 yen off the enrollment fee.]]></description>
        </item>
        <item>
            <title><![CDATA[Is Hitooshi Expensive? Total Cost of the Enrollment & Monthly Fees, and How to Save 5,000 Yen]]></title>
            <link>https://ryotablog.jp/en/blogs/zakki/hitooshi-price</link>
            <guid>hitooshi-price</guid>
            <pubDate>Sun, 20 Apr 2025 06:06:00 GMT</pubDate>
            <description><![CDATA[A real, numbers-based breakdown of the marriage-hunting service "Hitooshi." Covers the 17,800 yen enrollment fee + 17,800 yen monthly fee with zero success fee, a 3/6/12-month total-cost simulation, a comparison against matching apps and traditional marriage agencies, and how to save 5,000 yen with a referral code.]]></description>
        </item>
        <item>
            <title><![CDATA[What Is Hitooshi Marriage-Hunting? How It Differs from Apps and Agencies, and Who It Suits]]></title>
            <link>https://ryotablog.jp/en/blogs/zakki/hitooshi-konkatsu</link>
            <guid>hitooshi-konkatsu</guid>
            <pubDate>Tue, 09 Jun 2026 07:04:04 GMT</pubDate>
            <description><![CDATA[What is Hitooshi's marriage-hunting service? A former user neutrally explains how it works, the cost, how it differs from matching apps and marriage agencies, the member age range, and who it suits. With links to detailed review and interview articles.]]></description>
        </item>
        <item>
            <title><![CDATA[A Complete Guide to Bringing Your Own SSL Certificate to AWS Amplify Hosting (CSR, ACM Import, Terraform, and Verification)]]></title>
            <link>https://ryotablog.jp/en/blogs/aws/amplify-custom-ssl-acm-import</link>
            <guid>amplify-custom-ssl-acm-import</guid>
            <pubDate>Wed, 06 May 2026 08:35:36 GMT</pubDate>
            <description><![CDATA[A step-by-step guide to applying a custom SSL/TLS certificate (issued by a CA of your choice) to an AWS Amplify Hosting custom domain. Covers CSR creation, chain construction, integrity verification, Terraform configuration, post-deployment verification, and expiry monitoring — written so junior engineers can follow along.]]></description>
        </item>
